entry.name: http_req_per_request_trace_rule_matched
entry.text: ODR trace rule %1$d of type '%2$s' ('%3$s') matched request with url '%4$s:%5$d//%6$s '.
entry.summary: An inbound request matches a per-request trace rule of the On-Demand Router.
entry.description: An HTTP or HTTPS request having the specified URL matched a previously-defined On-Demand Router per-request trace enablement rule.
entry.suggestion: If this is not expected, examine the On-Demand Router trace rules you have defined to help determine why the named request matched.

entry.name: odr_state_change
entry.text: ODR library state changed from %1$s to %2$s, reason: %3$s
entry.summary: The ODR library state changed
entry.description: Informative message notifying of an ODR library state change
entry.suggestion: The ODR library state can change unexpectedly if it's connection to the REST service fails and failover occurs. If the ODR library remains in a state other than STARTED for an extended period of time, connectivity to WebSphere is not complete. This may happen if one of the cells to which the ODR library is connected is completely down.

entry.name: http_req_per_request_routing_rule_matched

entry.suggestion: If this is not expected, examine the On-Demand Router routing rules you have defined to help determine why the named request matched.

entry.name: http_req_parsing_error

entry.name: transitionpending

entry.suggestion: Verify the availability of IMS and IMS Connect. If the condition persists, contact IBM Support.
